3. Strings

What is a String?

s = "hello"


⸻

String Immutability

s = "hello"
# s[0] = "H" ❌ ERROR
s = "Hello"  # ✔ new string created


⸻

Concatenation

a = "Hello"
b = "World"
print(a + " " + b)


⸻

Interpolation (f-strings)

name = "slamdad"
print(f"Hello {name}")


⸻

String Slicing

s = "Python"
print(s[0:3])   # Pyt
print(s[-1])    # n


⸻

Common Methods

s = "hello"

print(s.upper())
print(s.lower())
print(s.strip())
print(s.replace("h", "H"))


⸻

4. Numbers & Operations

Integers & Floats

a = 10
b = 2.5


⸻

Arithmetic

print(a + b)
print(a - b)
print(a * b)
print(a / b)
print(a % 3)
print(a ** 2)


⸻

Augmented Assignment

x = 5
x += 2   # 7
x *= 3   # 21


⸻

5. Booleans & Conditionals

Boolean Values

True
False


⸻

Conditions

x = 10

if x > 5:
    print("Greater")
elif x == 5:
    print("Equal")
else:
    print("Smaller")


⸻

Logical Operators

if x > 5 and x < 20:
    print("Valid")


⸻

Truthy / Falsy

Falsy:

False, 0, "", None, [], {}

Truthy:

Everything else


⸻

Short Circuit

False and print("won't run")
True or print("won't run")


⸻

6. Functions & Scope

Function Basics

def greet():
    print("Hello")

greet()


⸻

With Parameters

def add(a, b):
    return a + b

print(add(2, 3))


⸻

Scope

x = 10  # global

def func():
    x = 5  # local
    print(x)

func()
print(x)


